00:15:49,759 --> 00:15:51,679
Wanting to get away from here?

241
00:15:53,799 --> 00:15:54,840
It was an odd time.

242
00:15:55,879 --> 00:15:57,519
After she died. Becky.

243
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:01,600
Me mum did go a bit mental.

244
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,759
Me dad couldn't stand it either.
He left.

245
00:16:05,759 --> 00:16:06,840
How old were you?

246
00:16:07,879 --> 00:16:11,720
20. She said some really stupid
things.

247
00:16:14,559 --> 00:16:16,200
But, you know, she was ill.

248
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,840
I think she's fantast...

249
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,360
Oh, God.

250
00:16:26,519 --> 00:16:27,879
What?

251
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:33,840
I just remembered something
I said last night, to her.

252
00:16:38,879 --> 00:16:40,200
Moving on...

253
00:16:41,639 --> 00:16:44,159
How was last night?
Did it do the trick?

254
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:46,679
What trick?

255
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,278
Cheer you up.

256
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:51,318
Cheer ME up?

257
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,399
Yeah.

258
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,318
Have I put me foot in it?

259
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,399
The bastards!

260
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,759
You OK?

261
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:11,319
It was silly what upset me. I
haven't told anyone. It was at work.

262
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:17,118
This... bloke asked me out for a
drink. A detective.

263
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,278
Nothing special,
old enough to be me dad,

264
00:17:19,279 --> 00:17:23,759
and I knew he was married and been
having an affair with someone else.

265
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,839
But I quite liked him.

266
00:17:30,079 --> 00:17:34,439
It was the first time I'd thought
about... the possibility of...

267
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,759
you know.

268
00:17:37,519 --> 00:17:38,920
Being close to someone.

269
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,160
Since what happened to me.

270
00:17:44,759 --> 00:17:47,079
So it was a big deal.
Not that he knew that.

271
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,440
Then...

272
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,680
...he didn't turn up.

273
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:55,759
So...

274
00:17:57,759 --> 00:17:58,920
Tosser.

275
00:18:01,279 --> 00:18:02,680
Yeah.

276
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,880
Space Oddity
by David Bowie

277
00:18:16,119 --> 00:18:21,358
- '..losing 20 pounds and having
great sex for the rest of your life,
tied with just 22%...'

278
00:18:21,359 --> 00:18:23,638
Don't Stop Me Now
by Queen

279
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,519
♪ Like Lady Godiva

280
00:18:25,519 --> 00:18:29,878
♪ I'm gonna go, go, go
There's no stopping me... ♪

281
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,038
Jack!

282
00:18:34,039 --> 00:18:35,118
'Hiya.'

283
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,479
It's me, Dad.

284
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,519
'You all right?'

285
00:18:37,519 --> 00:18:42,118
Listen... Erm... I'm coming home.
Are you going to let me in?

286
00:18:42,119 --> 00:18:43,838
'Yeah. Yeah, yeah.'

287
00:18:43,839 --> 00:18:44,880
Cheers, mate.

288
00:18:54,079 --> 00:18:55,759
Cheers, pal.

289
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:58,959
So! Hello. Good morning!

290
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,680
How are we all?

291
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:03,679
Good(!)

292
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,638
So I've got a little proposal
I'd like to put to you.

293
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,398
Contrary to what you think,

294
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,318
I'm not the one who's been having
some sort of sordid little fling

295
00:19:11,319 --> 00:19:15,719
with some sad sod from Mirfield who
drives a Skoda - no, that'll be you.

296
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:18,638
So what I'm proposing is,
YOU move out,

297
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,719
you gather your bits and pieces,
you move in with loverboy,

298
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,679
you feel free
to do whatever you have to do.

299
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:27,118
I - me - the one who hasn't been
mucking about -

300
00:19:27,119 --> 00:19:31,358
will stay here, in our house, with
our children. How about that?

301
00:19:31,359 --> 00:19:32,798
I'm not leaving the children.

302
00:19:32,799 --> 00:19:34,638
Yeah. Well, newsflash.
Neither am I.

303
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:37,358
And you're a liar. I know damn
well you've been up to something.

304
00:19:37,359 --> 00:19:41,638
OK, then. Who is this mysterious
whoever who I've been having this
relationship with, then? Eh?

305
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:46,358
Where is she? Eh? She doesn't exist,
Amanda. She's in your head!

306
00:19:46,359 --> 00:19:52,118
And you really should get your facts
straight before you start
accusing people of things.

307
00:19:52,119 --> 00:19:55,719
Now go and pack your stuff and ring
Casanova. He'll be thrilled!

308
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:59,519
You can set up home together.
That's the plan, isn't it?

309
00:19:59,519 --> 00:20:01,679
I assume that's the plan.

310
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,439
Does Graham know that's the plan?

311
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:04,798
Shut up!

312
00:20:04,799 --> 00:20:06,318
Oh! Does he not?

313
00:20:08,599 --> 00:20:10,999
Oh, does he not?

314
00:20:13,039 --> 00:20:16,838
Can we talk about this sensibly,
properly,

315
00:20:16,839 --> 00:20:19,038
not in front of the children?

316
00:20:19,039 --> 00:20:21,078
Perhaps I should go
and tell him, then.

317
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:23,159
Perhaps I should keep him informed.

318
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:25,558
Perhaps I should knock his
teeth down his throat.

319
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:26,638
Where you going?

320
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,719
Mirfield.

321
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:29,038
You don't know where he lives.

322
00:20:29,039 --> 00:20:31,439
I'm a detective, love.
I know bloody well where he lives.

323
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:34,318
Feel free to ring ahead and warn him
that I'm on my way.

324
00:20:34,319 --> 00:20:37,798
If he's not in when I get there,
I'll ask his wife to pass on a
message. How about that?

325
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:40,159
No. Don't do that! John! Don't!

326
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:42,519
What, does she not know either?

327
00:20:43,519 --> 00:20:48,919
So it's just you that thinks the
two of you's slinking off into the
sunset together, is it?

328
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,479
I shan't be long, kids.

329
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,558
Dad!

330
00:20:51,559 --> 00:20:53,240
Shan't be long, tiddler!

331
00:20:54,839 --> 00:20:55,999
Why did you let him in?

332
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,638
It's his house too, he lives here
as well!

333
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,680
Shit!

334
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,439
How many seconds?

335
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,838
I didn't even bother to count.

336
00:21:10,839 --> 00:21:13,159
You're supposed to count!

337
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,398
- Two and a half?
- It was nearly a minute!

338
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,598
And the rest!

339
00:21:16,599 --> 00:21:18,200
I'll have to do it again now.

340
00:21:19,759 --> 00:21:20,838
Good morning!

341
00:21:20,839 --> 00:21:21,999
Granny!

342
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,118
Hi!

343
00:21:23,119 --> 00:21:25,398
Count how long I can balance!

344
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,759
Did you sleep all right?

345
00:21:26,759 --> 00:21:29,078
- Granny!
- Yeah, yeah. Thanks. Sorry.

346
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:31,479
I'll drive you home in a bit.
Have you had some breakfast?

347
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,720
Just had some coffee.

348
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:39,159
Well, I got it. 149.99.

349
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,440
I don't want it.

350
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,038
What are you talking about?

351
00:21:45,039 --> 00:21:46,439
I'll have it!

352
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,919
What d'you mean, you don't want it?

353
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:50,318
- I mean, I don't want it.
- Why?
- Because it's not the same.

354
00:21:50,319 --> 00:21:52,999
It's exactly the same. Only
we know where this one's come from.

355
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,078
I wanted that other one.

356
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:57,078
Well, you couldn't have that other
one, and I promised I'd replace it.

357
00:21:57,079 --> 00:21:58,359
I wanted the one me dad sent.

358
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:06,278
He's not your dad.
I've explained this.

359
00:22:06,279 --> 00:22:07,558
Yeah. But he is.

360
00:22:07,559 --> 00:22:09,078
Why don't I go and set it up?

361
00:22:09,079 --> 00:22:11,318
And you go ring Cesco to come round
and have a race.

362
00:22:11,319 --> 00:22:12,598
We'll have a championship.

363
00:22:12,599 --> 00:22:13,638
No.

364
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:14,759
I'll set it up.

365
00:22:14,759 --> 00:22:17,278
No, if he's not going to play with
it, I'll get my money back.

366
00:22:17,279 --> 00:22:19,599
- He'll play with it.
- I shan't.

367
00:22:46,519 --> 00:22:47,919
Sorry.

368
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,118
It's fine.

369
00:22:49,119 --> 00:22:51,239
Oh, it's ridiculous.
It's impossible.

370
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:53,199
You need to find out who
put it there.

371
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,358
I will, I'm going to.

372
00:22:54,359 --> 00:22:55,479
Bastard.

373
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,160
Don't get me started.

374
00:23:01,119 --> 00:23:03,479
I'm sorry
if I was talking shite last night.

375
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,400
No, you weren't. You were happy.

376
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:11,078
Oh, I got you this.
From the chemist.

377
00:23:11,079 --> 00:23:12,278
What is it?

378
00:23:12,279 --> 00:23:13,440
Morning after pill.

379
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,118
Oh, Jesus.

380
00:23:16,119 --> 00:23:19,719
I mean, I don't know that you need
it, I don't know what you did,
but I just thought...

381
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:20,798
Thanks.

382
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:21,959
- You know.
- Yeah.

383
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:24,159
- Just in case.
- How much do I owe you?

384
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:28,318
It's fine, it's nothing, it's a
present. Except you do know,
just for future reference,

385
00:23:28,319 --> 00:23:31,719
if anyone'd seen you, it would've
been a Public Order offence
at the very least,

386
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,759
and you'd have lost your job.

387
00:23:35,599 --> 00:23:36,839
Shit, can you answer that?

388
00:23:41,759 --> 00:23:45,959
Hello, Catherine's phone? She's
driving, she's just dropping me
home.

389
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:48,479
Yeah, all right, bye.

390
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:51,598
She says, can you pop up to the
allotment after you've
dropped me off?

391
00:23:51,599 --> 00:23:53,000
Deep joy(!)

392
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,278
So what's up?

393
00:24:10,279 --> 00:24:16,878
Well, I've been expecting Neil all
morning but he's not shown up.

394
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,318
I knocked on his door on my way
down, no answer,

395
00:24:19,319 --> 00:24:21,479
I've phoned him,
I've texted him, nothing.

396
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:24,078
And it's odd cos
we were reckoning to spend

397
00:24:24,079 --> 00:24:25,638
the day on the allotment together.

398
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:26,878
He'll have forgotten.

399
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:28,118
It's not like him.

400
00:24:28,119 --> 00:24:30,239
- I wouldn't know.
- Why don't you like him?

401
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,278
It's only lunchtime.

402
00:24:32,279 --> 00:24:34,798
He's a really nice man.

403
00:24:34,799 --> 00:24:36,038
So what wants doing?

404
00:24:36,039 --> 00:24:37,719
I've got all these planks to shift.

405
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,318
Jerry at far end said
he'd have 'em.

406
00:24:39,319 --> 00:24:41,679
Well, can't Jerry at far end come
and fetch 'em?

407
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,079
He's in hospital.

408
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:48,599
Hey. They've charged that fella.

409
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,959
Sean Balmforth. This morning.
It's been on t'radio.

410
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:55,159
They've charged him wi' them
murders.

411
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,398
Wow.

412
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,960
I know.

413
00:25:03,079 --> 00:25:04,798
You all right?

414
00:25:04,799 --> 00:25:07,638
I bought our Ryan that Scalextric
and he reckoned he didn't want it.

415
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:09,159
"I wanted that one me dad sent me."

416
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:11,719
I've said it till I'm blue
in the face, "He's not your dad."

417
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:13,440
And he goes, "Yeah, but he is."

418
00:25:15,079 --> 00:25:16,720
It'll never go away, will it?

419
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:24,078
When I find out which sad, twisted
sod left that on our doorstep...

420
00:25:24,079 --> 00:25:26,480
I'll make
'em wish they'd never been born.

421
00:26:44,519 --> 00:26:47,319
- Nice weekend?
- Yourself?

422
00:26:49,079 --> 00:26:50,638
Have you heard owt from Gravesend?

423
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:53,398
Yes! I did. Late on Friday night,
they sent a list.

424
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:56,999
Visitors, phone calls,
people he writes to.
I can't let you see it.

425
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,159
You being funny?

426
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,638
No. I can't have you taking
the law into your own hands.

427
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:04,999
- What, Friday night and you didn't
let me know?
- I've forwarded the list
to an analyst in the DIU.

428
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,398
He'll gather intel on all of 'em,

429
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:09,199
and as soon as we know anything
significant, I'll get back to you.

430
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:12,599
You know that's the right way
forward, Catherine,
don't start pulling faces.

431
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:17,519
Woman in the toy shop in Hebden
last week buying a Scalextric.

432
00:27:17,519 --> 00:27:19,519
Exactly the same model.

433
00:27:19,519 --> 00:27:23,278
I went in and asked the fella
behind the counter on Saturday
and he showed me his CCTV.

434
00:27:23,279 --> 00:27:24,519
Looks like a lad.

435
00:27:24,519 --> 00:27:26,358
Yeah, well, it's a woman,
the fella said.

436
00:27:26,359 --> 00:27:30,439
- Either way, it doesn't mean it's
whoever it was left it on your
doorstep.
- No, I know that,

437
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:33,118
but was there anyone on the list
from round here?

438
00:27:33,119 --> 00:27:34,838
No.

439
00:27:34,839 --> 00:27:36,159
Not?

440
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:38,279
No. Not from round here.

441
00:27:40,799 --> 00:27:42,838
Are you briefing t'troops?

442
00:27:42,839 --> 00:27:45,759
Yes, I am. Are you saying,
"Well done, Catherine"?

443
00:27:45,759 --> 00:27:46,919
What for this time?

444
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:50,239
Sean Balmforth. Charged.
That was me got him arrested.

445
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,878
Oh! Yes, but...

446
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:54,398
They're playing it down
till it's confirmed,

447
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:57,519
but there's another body
turned up in Rastrick.

448
00:27:57,519 --> 00:27:59,199
When?

449
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,558
Early hours this morning.

450
00:28:01,559 --> 00:28:03,999
And depending on when she died...

451
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:06,319
it could mean they've charged
the wrong fella.

452
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,318
- Sorry!
- Mornin'.

453
00:28:17,319 --> 00:28:21,759
Oh, congratulations! He's been
charged, you'll have heard.
That fella you tipped us off about.

454
00:28:21,759 --> 00:28:25,439
Oh, have you not heard?
Apparently another body's turned up.

455
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:26,959
Did you not know?

456
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:28,319
It's what I've just been told.

457
00:28:30,839 --> 00:28:32,798
Good morning, you lucky people...

458
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,240
(Bollocks.)

459
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,479
Really?

460
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,119
(Shit.)

461
00:29:05,359 --> 00:29:08,519
She thinks she's not been dead
more than 48 hours.

462
00:29:08,519 --> 00:29:10,598
She'll be more specific
at the postmortem,

463
00:29:10,599 --> 00:29:13,358
but it's looking like she died after
we had Sean in custody.

464
00:29:13,359 --> 00:29:15,400
- Oh, f...
- I know.

465
00:29:27,559 --> 00:29:28,880
Could it be a copycat?

466
00:29:31,039 --> 00:29:34,519
Well, again, we'll know more
after the PM, but...

467
00:29:42,039 --> 00:29:46,398
So, we'll be getting
the review team in.

468
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:48,959
And to restore public confidence
in the investigation,

469
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:53,359
I'll be getting my arse kicked
down the stairs in the traditional
manner, no doubt, by your dad.

470
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:56,599
I can only apologise.

471
00:30:00,519 --> 00:30:02,000
Who is she?

472
00:30:04,599 --> 00:30:08,119
White. Between 20 and 30.
Poor teeth, poor clothes.

473
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:18,638
You know, the only thing I'd have
done differently from you
on Saturday...

474
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,598
I'm sorry, do you want to hear this?

475
00:30:20,599 --> 00:30:23,480
You wouldn't have charged him
with Vicky Fleming.

476
00:30:31,359 --> 00:30:36,200
"'I'm sure that dog's getting
bigger by the minute, ' said Dad.

477
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:39,679
"Ben and Albert laughed.

478
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:41,799
"'If only Dad knew.'"

479
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:47,078
You're doing so well.
Ben and Albert!

480
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:49,239
They remind me of you and Cesco.

481
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,598
How?

482
00:30:50,599 --> 00:30:52,398
Just, you're best friends.

483
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:53,638
Oh, yeah.

484
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,719
Do you and Cesco do sleepovers?

485
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,558
I used to love sleepovers!

486
00:30:57,559 --> 00:31:00,078
That's the best thing
about a best friend.

487
00:31:00,079 --> 00:31:03,118
- Sometimes we do.
- Yeah? Have you got one planned?

488
00:31:03,119 --> 00:31:04,159
