00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,679
You can speak to me, you know, Neil.

739
00:45:01,679 --> 00:45:04,719
I know what alcohol does to people,
I see it every day.

740
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:07,918
I know you're not like that.

741
00:45:07,920 --> 00:45:10,880
I mean, I know you don't want
to be like that.

742
00:45:12,280 --> 00:45:13,760
I'm sorry.

743
00:45:17,280 --> 00:45:18,719
Come on.

744
00:45:24,760 --> 00:45:27,679
Have you fallen off the wagon
before, since you've been dry?

745
00:45:27,679 --> 00:45:29,400
Twice.

746
00:45:32,119 --> 00:45:33,559
OK, well...

747
00:45:34,719 --> 00:45:37,280
...you tell me what I can do
to support you.

748
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:42,199
You know yourself best, you know
your habits. What do you need?
What can I do?

749
00:45:42,199 --> 00:45:44,639
Catherine, I just want to go home,

750
00:45:44,639 --> 00:45:47,079
want to get a shower,
get rid of this headache,

751
00:45:47,079 --> 00:45:49,000
get back to normal,
put it behind me.

752
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:53,438
Did you ring in sick at work?

753
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:54,998
You didn't just go AWOL?

754
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:56,239
I took three days off.

755
00:45:57,239 --> 00:46:00,880
You see, when I know the way
things are going - up here...

756
00:46:04,519 --> 00:46:06,360
...I plan ahead.

757
00:46:13,880 --> 00:46:15,039
(Right.)

758
00:46:21,760 --> 00:46:24,278
Well, just... I don't know what
triggers you, and I'm sorry

759
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:26,478
if you've got something upsetting
you at the minute

760
00:46:26,480 --> 00:46:27,518
that's sparked it off.

761
00:46:27,519 --> 00:46:29,958
But Clare's vulnerable too,
and she's my priority,

762
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:32,838
and I won't watch her get
dragged down. Not by anyone.

763
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:35,199
I'm sorry if you think
I've not been very friendly.

764
00:46:35,199 --> 00:46:38,239
I am sorry. She's very fond of you
and I want to respect that,
all right?

765
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:39,880
But please don't mess her about.

766
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:43,199
I won't.

767
00:47:18,079 --> 00:47:19,998
Three days?

768
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,798
What, and then he can just stop?

769
00:47:21,800 --> 00:47:23,239
I don't know.

770
00:47:23,239 --> 00:47:26,798
D'you think it's good for her?
Being with someone who's the same?

771
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:28,998
What can I do? She's grown up.

772
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:32,918
You think they'll be all right
together on their own in his flat?

773
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:35,759
I mean, it isn't five minutes since
she... fell off the wagon, is it?

774
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:36,878
No, they're coming here.

775
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:39,639
He's gone to tidy himself up,
then they're going to an AA meeting

776
00:47:39,639 --> 00:47:41,599
in Halifax, then they're coming
here.

777
00:47:41,599 --> 00:47:46,318
That WOULD worry me. If ever they
did decide to move in together.

778
00:47:46,320 --> 00:47:49,639
It wouldn't have till today, but,
my God, you should have seen him.

779
00:47:49,639 --> 00:47:51,719
Is this mental?

780
00:47:51,719 --> 00:47:53,599
What?

781
00:47:53,599 --> 00:47:55,478
Three days, he's been pissed.

782
00:47:55,480 --> 00:47:57,798
Disappeared, God knows where.

783
00:47:57,800 --> 00:48:01,159
And then another one of these women
has been murdered.

784
00:48:02,679 --> 00:48:04,679
Why would you think that about him?

785
00:48:06,760 --> 00:48:10,079
- He's really uncomfortable
around you.
- Yeah, I know,

786
00:48:10,079 --> 00:48:11,679
but that could just...

787
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:15,159
...be my effortless
overwhelming charisma.

788
00:48:16,639 --> 00:48:18,440
Yeah, and that, obviously.

789
00:48:19,519 --> 00:48:21,079
It IS mental.

790
00:48:21,079 --> 00:48:22,438
I know it's mental.

791
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:25,239
When the Ripper was around,
everybody was thinking it was

792
00:48:25,239 --> 00:48:28,759
their husband and their son
and their dad and their uncle.

793
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:31,239
Yeah, but... It's someone.

794
00:48:33,960 --> 00:48:36,239
And the other thing.

795
00:48:36,239 --> 00:48:38,719
Ryan was asking about Becky.

796
00:48:38,719 --> 00:48:40,360
After you went out.

797
00:48:41,440 --> 00:48:43,320
About her relationship with...

798
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:45,719
...him.

799
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:49,918
I didn't say owt. I just said
she was infatuated

800
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:53,119
and she didn't really know what
he was like, but it struck me -

801
00:48:53,119 --> 00:48:55,559
it's when he gets home from school.

802
00:48:55,559 --> 00:48:58,559
That's when he's got a new thing,
a new question,

803
00:48:58,559 --> 00:49:01,079
like someone's put ideas
in his head.

804
00:49:01,079 --> 00:49:02,759
At school?

805
00:49:02,760 --> 00:49:04,119
Yeah.

806
00:49:23,599 --> 00:49:25,079
Mum?

807
00:49:27,559 --> 00:49:28,960
Mum?

808
00:49:30,480 --> 00:49:32,159
Mum.

809
00:49:38,519 --> 00:49:41,358
Mum, I need to talk to you, Mum.

810
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:43,440
What's the matter?

811
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:47,119
I don't feel so well.

812
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:50,398
What is it?

813
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:51,960
Headache?

814
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:56,199
I don't want to go and tell
the police about me car.

815
00:50:02,800 --> 00:50:05,079
OK.

816
00:50:05,079 --> 00:50:06,400
Is that OK?

817
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:10,599
Why?

818
00:50:13,280 --> 00:50:14,719
Why don't you want to?

819
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:21,280
Because...

820
00:50:22,519 --> 00:50:24,320
...I've done things.

821
00:50:25,719 --> 00:50:27,039
What things?

822
00:50:28,519 --> 00:50:30,199
Things.

823
00:50:30,199 --> 00:50:31,599
What things?

824
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,440
I think you'll be cross.

825
00:50:37,320 --> 00:50:39,840
No, don't turn the light on.
Do you mind?

826
00:50:46,519 --> 00:50:48,719
What is it you've done, love?

827
00:50:51,039 --> 00:50:53,998
You know you can tell me anything.

828
00:50:54,000 --> 00:50:56,480
I've always said that. Haven't I?

829
00:50:58,039 --> 00:51:01,159
If you tell me the truth,
I won't be cross. About anything.

830
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:04,518
Yeah.

831
00:51:04,519 --> 00:51:06,280
Well, then...

832
00:51:10,199 --> 00:51:12,239
I...

833
00:51:14,920 --> 00:51:16,239
Have you hurt someone?

834
00:51:17,480 --> 00:51:19,119
Yeah.

835
00:51:19,119 --> 00:51:21,639
With your car?

836
00:51:21,639 --> 00:51:22,960
No.

837
00:51:24,199 --> 00:51:25,519
Is it...?

838
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:32,559
Is it to do with those women?

839
00:51:32,559 --> 00:51:34,239
Why you saying that?

840
00:51:34,239 --> 00:51:36,878
- Is it?
- Why you saying that?!

841
00:51:36,880 --> 00:51:38,639
Because...

842
00:51:38,639 --> 00:51:40,398
- I wondered.
- Had you? When?

843
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:41,918
A while back.

844
00:51:41,920 --> 00:51:43,360
Why didn't you tell me?

845
00:51:50,719 --> 00:51:52,679
If it was...

846
00:51:52,679 --> 00:51:54,239
would you tell the police?

847
00:51:55,239 --> 00:51:57,159
Well, would you want me to?

848
00:51:58,320 --> 00:51:59,719
No.

849
00:52:01,679 --> 00:52:04,079
I just...
I don't know what I'd do

850
00:52:04,079 --> 00:52:06,518
if they came looking for me.

851
00:52:06,519 --> 00:52:09,039
The thing is,
they've got my DNA now,

852
00:52:09,039 --> 00:52:10,918
cos of that fight the other day.

853
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:13,239
And I'd not get far if I set off.

854
00:52:13,239 --> 00:52:14,760
Why?!

855
00:52:17,480 --> 00:52:19,239
Why did you?

856
00:52:29,199 --> 00:52:31,918
Why, though?

857
00:52:31,920 --> 00:52:33,519
I don't know.

858
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:42,679
We've had a funny life,
haven't we, lad?

859
00:53:04,960 --> 00:53:06,400
What you thinking?

860
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:11,480
I don't know.

861
00:53:13,880 --> 00:53:16,559
I'm wondering
if there's a way forward.

862
00:53:18,159 --> 00:53:19,880
If we could get rid of the car.

863
00:53:21,119 --> 00:53:24,199
But then, there's 1,001
other things to think about.

864
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:31,800
Are you sure it was you?

865
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,719
Did someone tell you to do it?

866
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:42,318
No.

867
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:43,360
Voices?

868
00:53:45,239 --> 00:53:46,759
No.

869
00:53:46,760 --> 00:53:49,838
Sometimes people hear voices
telling 'em to do stuff.

870
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:51,199
No.

871
00:53:58,199 --> 00:53:59,679
OK.

872
00:54:10,239 --> 00:54:13,039
You'll visit me, won't you,
in prison?

873
00:54:14,440 --> 00:54:16,519
I don't think you'd like prison.

874
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:22,519
No, but if you can't think of
anything, then it's what'll happen.

875
00:54:52,400 --> 00:54:53,958
How's Neil?

876
00:54:53,960 --> 00:54:55,478
He's gone to work.

877
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:58,880
- Oh, good.
- Half six this morning.

878
00:55:00,119 --> 00:55:02,358
That's good.

879
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:04,679
Hey, have you run that theory
past Clare, Mum?

880
00:55:04,679 --> 00:55:06,599
- What theory?
- Which?

881
00:55:06,599 --> 00:55:08,398
That woman on your phone.

882
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:11,278
Oh, yeah! You know a couple of
weeks ago,

883
00:55:11,280 --> 00:55:14,159
that new Miss Wealand, Whelan -
whatever her name is.

884
00:55:14,159 --> 00:55:16,639
Asking Ryan questions
about his dad.

885
00:55:16,639 --> 00:55:18,239
Yeah.

886
00:55:18,239 --> 00:55:21,719
Daniel reckons it's always
when he comes home from school

887
00:55:21,719 --> 00:55:24,119
that he starts asking
questions about him.

888
00:55:24,119 --> 00:55:27,239
- Is it?
- Yeah.
- Have you met her?

889
00:55:27,239 --> 00:55:28,840
Yeah, I told you I had.

890
00:55:33,239 --> 00:55:35,039
Where's your glasses?

891
00:55:36,440 --> 00:55:37,679
Isn't that a lad?

892
00:55:38,719 --> 00:55:41,280
No, it's a woman.
The man in the shop said.

893
00:55:48,559 --> 00:55:50,878
What you thinking?

894
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:52,159
I'm thinking...

895
00:55:53,159 --> 00:55:54,559
What?

896
00:55:57,159 --> 00:55:58,719
It's her.

897
00:56:25,599 --> 00:56:27,159
This is nice.

898
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:29,998
I've got a plan.

899
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:31,878
Have you?

900
00:56:31,880 --> 00:56:35,559
You've always wanted to go
to America, haven't you?

901
00:56:35,559 --> 00:56:37,438
How we going to afford that?

902
00:56:37,440 --> 00:56:40,518
I've got some money put by.
Quite a bit.

903
00:56:40,519 --> 00:56:41,798
How much?

904
00:56:41,800 --> 00:56:43,759
Couple of thousand.

905
00:56:43,760 --> 00:56:45,599
We've got our passports.

906
00:56:45,599 --> 00:56:47,438
We'll call a taxi.

907
00:56:47,440 --> 00:56:49,358
Get on a train to Manchester.

908
00:56:49,360 --> 00:56:51,159
Then we'll get on an aeroplane.

909
00:56:51,159 --> 00:56:55,159
And they might catch up with us
eventually - I think they very
probably would -

910
00:56:55,159 --> 00:56:58,159
but at least you'll have done
something.

911
00:56:58,159 --> 00:57:01,759
At least we'd have seen something
of the world, had an adventure,
wouldn't we?

912
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:03,318
Las Vegas?

913
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:05,278
Is that what you'd like?

914
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:09,000
Nevada. The desert.
Duke and Gonzo, we could hire a car.

915
00:57:13,639 --> 00:57:14,840
OK.

916
00:57:20,119 --> 00:57:21,760
Seriously?

917
00:57:31,760 --> 00:57:33,840
What else would you like to do?

918
00:57:34,880 --> 00:57:36,679
To see?

919
00:57:36,679 --> 00:57:39,278
- Florida.
- Yeah.

920
00:57:39,280 --> 00:57:41,599
- California.
- San Francisco.

921
00:57:43,159 --> 00:57:45,438
Who'll feed the sheep?

922
00:57:45,440 --> 00:57:46,960
I'll ask me sister.

923
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:51,880
We could cycle across
the Golden Gate Bridge.

924
00:57:52,880 --> 00:57:55,159
You can hire bicycles.

925
00:57:55,159 --> 00:57:57,318
I saw it on a travel programme.

926
00:57:57,320 --> 00:57:59,278
Will she do that?

927
00:57:59,280 --> 00:58:02,119
Yeah. I'll pay her.

928
00:58:02,119 --> 00:58:04,199
Then you can get the ferry back.

929
00:58:04,199 --> 00:58:06,039
Go past Alcatraz.

930
00:58:06,039 --> 00:58:07,719
Won't go there, though.

931
00:58:07,719 --> 00:58:09,199
Can we go to Disneyland?

932
00:58:09,199 --> 00:58:11,239
Course we can, love.
